<Author>sdcagoodlife
<Content>Clean, modern, but trains are loud.... Clean, modern, staff reasonably friendly. Located just a block away from a bus stop that will get you in from the airport for just 7 euro. I had read other reviews warning about the trains, so asked when I made the reservation if the room faced the rail lines. Was assured that it faced the street, so there would be no problem. Well, the windows faced the street, but the exterior wall was on the rail line and it was loud. Seems to be a commuter line, so only a few cars at a time and not all night, but did start up pretty early. Enjoyed dinner in the restaurant that's in the building (you need to exit the hotel and walk a door or two down) our first night there 
