<Author>acc-tou
<Content>This is really a great place I had such a good time at this hotel in the summer of 2007 and feel that some of the negative reviews are not doing justice to the institution. My husband and I stayed for 3 nights, two at a newly renovated building and one at the old one. Unfortunately, the latter is not equipped with air conditioning and double glazing. Maybe that's why some gave out such harsh reviews. But the rooms in the new building are just amazing. Our room decorated as a bird's nest overlooked the parliament building, which was fantastic at night. And the room was right next to the train track but we could not hear a thing with the window closed. I remember my husband marveling at the German technology! The room becomes cold as soon as you turn the air conditioner on. The lobby is very arty, the backyard picturesque, and the location great. This hotel deserves much more than 3.5. Do not let negative reviews discourage you. 
