<Author>m_h72
<Content>Great location, but you better love trains My partner and I just stayed at the Arte Luise Kunsthotel in Berlin. It sells itself as one of Berlin's cool, artist-designed hotels, and we were looking forward to staying in a unique room with an individual design, near to the thriving centre of Berlin. The hotel certainly has a fantastic location, 5 minutes taxi ride from the Hauptbahnhof, and 5 minutes walk from the Reichstag and Brandenburg Gate. However, the room was a disappointment - large, but with somewhat damaged art on the walls, and the noise from passing trains was pretty overwhelming at first (the hotel is virtually on the line between the Hauptbahnhof and Friedrichstrasse). You know it must be noisy when the hotel supplies earplugs in the room... In its defence, you do get used to sleeping with the earplugs, the surrounding neighbourhood has some great cafes, and it's only about 90 euros a night (which is cheap for a hotel in the Mitte district). I also suspect if we had paid for a more expensive room, we would have been more sheltered from the street/train noise. Takeaway lesson: if you want to appreciate the art and the location, trade up for a swankier room and ask about noise when booking. 
