<Author>Nashville1
<Content>A great place to stay We stayed at the Art Luise for six nights at the end of June. There are really two separate hotels--the new wing in which we stayed and the older section. They are completely different places. The rooms in the new wing are very modern with excellent sound proofing and a very good central a/c system. There is a elevator. Even though the rooms are next to the train tracks, we had no problem with the noise. The hotel spent quite a bit of money on the sound proofing and it works. The odd thing is that automatic blinds were installed outside the windows. They do not do a very good job of keeping out the light--that was a far bigger problem than the noise. Also the rooms do not have clocks. Bring your travel alarm or have a cell phone that works in Germany because we did not get our wake up call to either room for our early flight home. The location is great--a 5 or 10 minute walk to Friedrichstrasse station with lots of good local restaurants along the way. We would definitely stay (in the new wing) again. 
