<Author>justwundering
<Content>Not for everyone This is a clean, friendly hotel but it is not for everyone. There is no elevator in the 'old' section of the hotel so if you are on the top floor--expect to carry your luggage up three flights of stairs (there isn't a door man or bell hop to assist you). I am not quite sure if they have an elevator in the new section of the hotel so check before you register if this is an issue for you.As one individual mentioned, the train tracks are located near the hotel so if you are a light sleeper - bring earplugs.Also, there were some rooms that were single rooms with one bed (you would need to share a bathroom). Our room had a small clean bathroom adjacent to our room.On the plus side, the staff was very friendly and helpful-probably one of the best during our two week stay in Germany. The location is great - easy walking distance to some of the main attractions, obviously near the train station, and a short walk to the bus terminal. The breakfast was served in a restaurant next door which served cereal, fruit, cheese, meats, and great German bread. The hotel is suited for older children but may be difficult for someone with small children. I believe it is a hotel suited for couples on vacation and business travelers.The art throughout the hotel would be classified as 'very modern'. We had a 'minimalist' room which was a fairly accurate description. My husband would stay here again but it would not be my first choice. It's a nice hotel but definetly not for everyone. 
