<Content>This is a great hotel! We stayed at the Kunstlerheim Luise for our first 2 nights in Berlin--what a great way to start! Our 2 rooms had very different art installations in them (our daughters chose the one outfitted like a giant seagull's nest, complete with hovering beak and huge eggs). We also asked for rooms with air-conditioning, for which we were very grateful during the recent heat wave. Our rooms were on the S-bahn side 2 floors up; other reviews have noted that this side can be noisy from the trains, but we could barely hear them. Breakfast in the adjoining restaurant is wonderful (and enjoys the occasional shake from the trains going by at this level). The hotel is near the Friedrichstrasse bahnhof and convenient for travel, shopping and restaurants. Staff was very pleasant, beds were beautiful and comfortable, and bathrooms were pristine. Can't wait to go back. 
