<Author>xxxooo
<Content>Stay here! This past December we stayed twice at the Hotel Kunstler Luise in Berlin, having stayed there once before four years ago. They offer a variety of accomodations, from singles to suites, and every room is decorated differently by local artists. We spent five days there, through New Years Eve, before going to Dresden, and stayed there again on our return. All of the front desk staff speaks english, and are extremely cordial. They allowed me to use the internet system located at the front desk for checking email, flight information, etc. As long as you're not greedy with time, there's no charge. The location provides easy access to the subway system, as well as a good selection of nearby restaurants. Each room has a unique artistic flavor, and the beds are quite comfortable. In fact, you can see images of the rooms on their website and request specific artists. A good buffet breakfast, consisting of breads, eggs, bacon, fruit, yogurt, etc., can be had in the restaurant next door (8 euros). I would highly recommend this hotel to anyone as it's both charming and affordable. 
