<Content>Excellent hotel My son picked this hotel out of the Lonely Planet book on Berlin. It had arrived that morning from Amazon. We were pleased to find that we were able to book two rooms on the 3rd floor without difficulty, although to get the configuration we required we could not get either with ensuite WC or shower. This didn't matter nearly as much as we anticipated as we seemed to be the only guests on the floor, certainly the only ones using the large shared bathroom.The place was warm, very well fitted out, almost completely free of smoke (possibly these were explicitly non-smoking rooms) and very interesting. Apart from a couple of bulbs that had blown the room was free of all defects. The stairs are a bit of a climb but this was probably a good thing considering the number of gut-busting meals we ate in Berlin over the tree days.Breakfast at WeinGuy next door was excellent with extremely friendly and efficient service. The croissants were the best I've tasted anywhere in Europe and certainly better than anything available in the UK.We paid about eur 420 for three nights for two rooms. 
